<br>
<br>
"Informed him that when people have really nice armor like this it usually means they are broke cause they spent all their money on their really nice armor."<br>
<br>
<br>
I just finished my ivy etched leggings quest last night (after almost 35 hours of camping Wiltin in OOT) and so there goes 200pp worth of bribes to get the NPC to accept the Quiver of Kithicor. I am now almost in full ivy (minus gloves) - I earned all my gear the hard way (with help from others, of course) and would not deny that feeling of pride to anyone else. <br>
<br>
<br>
"If I find someone getting ragged because they are actually trying to play the way the game was intended--from scratch, no twinking."<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm usually the one getting ragged on. Every time I start a newbie, I get the character *at least* to level 6 before I even consider passing any upgraded gear down. I've been picked on for having a level 5 wizard who couldn't even afford buying the rest of the level 1 spells. I've been picked on for being a level 9 warrior *still* wearing a full suit of tattered / patchwork armor (and that character had to make all the armor - tried for 3 real life days to get someone to make the armor for me, then gave up and started to train tailoring). And I was once a level 4 shadowknight wearing half a suit of tattered armor, getting KSed in Freeport by a level 2 dwarf with full crafted and a blade of xalgoz. Ugh, and it gets real annoying to have someone in their 50s walk up to me (the level 9 warrior in tattered, for example), inspect, and then start yelling at me because I'm not wearing bronze / crafted / cobalt / etc. Sorry beggars and twinkers, but I don't have 200k pp in the bank like everyone else. I'm just another poor ranger trying to enjoy the game...<br>
<br>
As for the beggars, I don't even bother responding to them anymore. I give buffs and money only to those people who I feel deserve them. I once tried to give a tailored large bag (6 slots, .8 weight) to a level 2 wizard and he started getting mad at me because he wanted plat. Gee, I was just trying to be nice. I eventually found someone who was shocked and excited to get such a gift; and face it, a free 6 slot bag is awesome when you are level 2. A few weeks ago I heard a level 5 bard in Freeport trying to sell some bog juice she had just made. Everyone was laughing at her - probably for doing trade skills, for "wasting her money", who knows... She was actually and untwinked newbie trying to earn a living with some snake scales she earned on the battlefield. I paid her 10pp for that stack of bog juice just because I was soooo happy to see a newbie trying to earn a living. <br>
<br>
Another thing that annoys me is the attitude that I get when I need a teleport or a res.  When I was level 26, I was fighting things in Lake of Ill Omen and monsters just started to *warp* on top of me from out of nowhere.  I died quick.  Then I appear in Firiona Vie and there are lots of people standing around.  I try for ten minutes to get a sow for corpse retrieval.  Nobody wants to help.  I give up and run to Ill Omen.  I shout what happened and ask for a res.  A cleric shouts back "oh that sucks".  I gave up, looted my corpse, and retired my ranger for two solid weeks.  When I came out of retirement, I headed for Kelethin, where I saw a ranger shouting for help - he got killed by the dragoon in WC and needed a port and some help to get his corpse back.  30 minutes later (with 9 non-anon people who could port in the zone), I offered to pay 15pp to tag along on the port and offered to help him get his corpse back - so now all that was required was a little mana to port us over there.  No response.  I saw a 51 wizard sitting near us, so I politely asked him if he had the time to port us.  No response.  I can take "sorry, too busy right now" - but he gave NO response.  I will laugh if he ever asks me for anything.  We eventually got a port - from a friend's druid who was 3 zones away - but it took almost two hours.  The problem is that I get this attitude from lots of people - I ask very politely if they can spare the time and/or mana to help me and I get NO response in return.  Please people, learn to recognize the difference between people like me and dewd beggars.<br>
<br>
Albarath says, "Excuse me sir, I was wondering if you could spare some mana to sow me for a corpse retrieval??"<br>
Kewldewd_00 says, "sowplzkkthx"<br>
<br>
Um, if you can't tell which person deserves at least a response, then I guess I'm just alone in my thoughts again...<br>
<br>
