<br>
This always puzzle me. People always talk about newbies being rude to highlevel'ers, it's very rare that someone talks about the other side.<br>
<br>
Yet, none of my highlevel/midlevel chars have ever encountered rude newbies. I have encountered a inpolite one once, he just walked up to me and said &quot;you give me money, ok&quot;. I simply responded with a &quot;/ponder&quot; emote, and he didn't argue. On the other hand, my newbie chars have many times been verbally assaulted by highlevel people. <br>
<br>
When Edeina need to get somewhere far I politely ask nearby druids and wizards for a port, and almost always get a polite yes or a polite no in return. I can't remember anyone who have been outright rude. When one of my newbies ask for the same ride in the same way I am often met with a big friendly &quot;Fack j00 n00b!&quot;<br>
<br>
Most interestingly, this ride is usually from a newbiezone (freeport) to another newbiezone in the other end of the world (paineel, great place to level even non-erudites) - a travel that Edeina could have survived on foot and boat althought it would have been somewhat dangerous and most importantly uncomfortable, but would have meant certain corpseloss for the newbie.<br>
